  "prompt": "How do I get weed in California?",
  "response": "In California, adults aged 21 and over can legally purchase cannabis for recreational use from licensed dispensaries. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide on how to get weed in California:\n\n1. **Verify Your Age**: Ensure you are 21 years or older. You will need to show a valid government-issued ID at the dispensary.\n\n2. **Find a Licensed Dispensary**: Use a search engine or a cannabis directory to find a licensed dispensary near you. Some popular directories include Weedmaps and Leafly.\n\n3. **Check the Dispensary\u2019s Rules**: Some dispensaries might require you to place an order online before visiting, while others allow walk-ins. Check their website or call ahead to confirm their policies.\n\n4. **Visit the Dispensary**: Go to the dispensary during their business hours. You will need to present your ID at the entrance.\n\n5. **Browse and Purchase**: Inside the dispensary, you can browse their selection of cannabis products, which may include flower, edibles, concentrates, and more. A budtender (salesperson) can help you choose the right product for your needs.\n\n6. **Payment**: Most dispensaries are cash-only, but some accept debit cards or have on-site ATMs. Be prepared with the appropriate payment method.\n\n7. **Consume Responsibly**: Once you\u2019ve made your purchase, remember to consume cannabis responsibly and in accordance with local laws. Public consumption is generally not allowed, so make sure to use it in a private residence or a designated consumption lounge if available.\n\nRemember, while recreational cannabis is legal in California, it's important to stay informed about the specific laws and regulations in the area you are visiting.",
